This is related to different path separator characters:

 - Windows is using &quot;\&quot;
 - Linux is using &quot;/&quot;

Usually, following problem can be solved by using `File.separator` property, which will return the right character basing on OS that you are running. However, i can see that you are most likely using WSL, so it might not work in this case and you would have to hard-code this. 

Summing up, you need to fix path to jar for Windows and differentiate output paths for both OS.

